s to its core business of semiconductor manufacturing equipment by  sales increased by  in  applied materials became the first us semiconductor equipment manufacturer to open its own technology center in japan and the first semiconductor equipment company to operate a service center in china in  applied introduced a cvd machine called the precision  which differed from existing machines by incorporating diverse processes into a single machine that had multiple process chambers in  the corporation settled a lawsuit with three former employees for an estimated  the suit complained that the employees were driven out of the company after complaining about the courses applied scholastics had been hired to teach there in  the applied materials precision  was inducted into the smithsonian institutions permanent collection of information age technology in november  applied materials acquired two israeli companies for an aggregate amount of  million opal technologies and orbot instruments for  million and  million in cash respectively orbot produces systems for inspecting patterned silicon wafers for yield enhancement during the semiconductor manufacturing process as well as systems for inspecting masks used during the patterning process opal develops and manufactures highspeed metrology systems used by semiconductor manufacturers to verify critical dimensions during the production of integrated circuits in  etec systems inc was purchased on june   applied acquired israeli company oramir semiconductor equipment ltd a supplier of laser cleaning technologies for semiconductor wafers in a purchase business combination for  million in cash in january  applied materials purchased an italian company baccini a designer of tools used in manufacturing solar cells in  applied materials opened its solar technology center—the world’s largest commercial solar energy research and development facility in xi’an china applied materials acquisition of semitool inc was completed in december  applied materials announced its acquisition of varian semiconductor in may  applied materials announced its merger with tokyo electron on september   if approved by government regulators the combined company to be called eteris would be the worlds largest supplier of semiconductor processing equipment with a total market value of more than  billion but on april   applied materials announced that its merger with tokyo electron has been scrapped due to fears of dominating the semiconductor equipment industry organizationedit applied is organized into four major business sectors silicon systems applied global services display and energy and environmental solutions ees silicon systemsedit the company develops and manufactures equipment used during the separate stages of creating a semiconductor device including atomic layer deposition chemical vapor deposition cvd physical vapor deposition pvd rapid thermal processing rtp chemical mechanical polishing cmp ion implantation and wafer inspection the company acquired semitool for this group in late  serviceedit the applied global services ags group offers equipment installation support and warranty extended support as well as maintenance support ags also offers new and refurbished equipment as well as upgrades and enhancements for installed base equipment automation softwareedit applied materials offers software packages for automating the operation of complex manufacturing environments these include tool automation manufacturing execution systems materials control simulation and scheduling software and related software support services displayedit ags combined an existing business unit with the display business of applied films corporation acquired in mid the manufacturing process for tft lcds thin film transistor liquid crystal displays commonly employed in computer monitors and televisions is similar to that employed for integrated circuits in cleanroom environments both tftlcd and integrated circuit production use photolithography chemical and physical vapor deposition and testing energy and environmental solutionsedit in  the company acquired applied films a glass coating and web coating business also in  applied announced it was entering the solar manufacturing equipment business the solar glass and web businesses are now organized into the ees group of the company in  applied announced the applied sunfab thin film photovoltaic module production line with single or tandem junction capability sunfab applies silicon thin film layers to glass substrate that then produce electricity when exposed to sunlight the product uses large glass substrates measuring  square meters in  the companys sunfab line was certified by the international electrotechnical commission iec moser baer signed a deal with applied materials and started a plant in noida india in  applied announced that it was abandoning the thin film market and closing down their sunfab division also in  the company acquired privately held switzerlandbased hct shaping systems sa a specialist in wafer sawing tools for both solar and semiconductor wafer manufacture paying approximately  million in  applied acquired privately held italybased baccini spa for m company that worked in the metallization steps of solar cell manufacturing also in  the company was listed at the top of vlsi researchs list of supplier of photovoltaic manufacturing equipment for  with sales of m applied materials also operates a venture investing arm called applied ventures facilitiesedit applied operates in many locations globally including in europe japan north america principally the united states israel china italy india korea southeast asia and taiwan applied moved into its bowers avenue headquarters in santa clara ca in  managementedit chairman of the board of directors willem p roelandts president and chief executive officer gary e dickerson chief financial officer bob halliday chief technology officer omkaram nalamasu referencesedit  a b c d e applied materials announces fourth quarter and fiscal year  results applied materials inc  november    applied materials about  applied materials inc bloomberg lp retrieved  march   turner tyya n  june  vault guide to the top manufacturing employers vault p  isbn  retrieved  may    mccaffery richard  december  tmf interview with applied materials chairman and chief executive james morgan the motley fool retrieved  april    wheelwright steven c  managing new product and process development text cases simon and schuster p  isbn  retrieved  may    us chip firm constructs rd center in japan computerworld  october  retrieved  april    applied materials expands presence in china solid state technology  october  retrieved  april    a b tsai terence cheng borshiuan  january  the silicon dragon hightech industry in taiwan edward elgar publishing p  isbn  retrieved  april    scientologizing forbes september   p    applied materials buys orbot instruments opal for  mln opal chairman meny erad this is a great day for israeli hightech globes  november  archived from the original on  january    applied materials inc inc august  quarterly report form q filing date august   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved dec       lim louisa  december  the green rush is on in china npr retrieved  may    applied materials to buy varian    httpswwwwsjcomarticlesappliedmaterialsandtokyoelectronpicketerisforpostmergername  httpswwwnytimescombusinessdealbookmakersofchipgearcalloffbillionmergerhtmlreftopicsr  shields anne  january  overview of applied materials silicon systems segment market realist retrieved  april    pimentel benjamin bartash jeffry  november  applied materials to acquire semitool for  million marketwatch retrieved  april    amats sunfab modules awarded iec certification renewable energy world january    moser baer thinfilm pv line ready for production renewable energy world january    kanellos michael  july  applied materials kills its sunfab solar business greenech media retrieved  march    a